assertDataFor(bytes32,bytes32,address).details: Data can be asserted many times with the same combination of arguments, resulting in unique assertionIds. returns.assertionId: The id of the generated Assertion.

params.assertionId: The identifier of the assertion that was resolved.

params.user: The address of a user that staked

params.forwarder: The contract address to be verified.

returns._0: bool Is the given address the trusted forwarder

postAssertion(bytes32,uint256,address,ui.details: about the asserter address: any address can be set as asserter, it will be expected to pay for the bond on posting. The bond tokens can also be deposited in the Module and used to pay for itself, but ONLY if the bond token is different from the one being used for staking. If the asserter is set to 0, whomever calls postAssertion will be paying the bond.

params.assertedValue: The target value that will be asserted and posted as data to the oracle
params.targetKPI: The KPI to be used for distribution once the assertion confirms

returns.assertionId: The assertionId received for the posted assertion

params._newCurrency: The address of the new default currency.
